at|mitche: Bidding: East has a pretty decent hand when West shows hearts, and she should "superaccept".

There are a couple of ways to superaccept: 
First, bid 3 hearts, to show a MINIMUM 1NT and 4 hearts. 
Second, with a MAXIMUM and 4333 shape with 4 Hearts, bid 2NT.  
Third, with a Doubleton, bid the short suit.  So here, the superaccept is 2@s.|
pg| ***** 36 ***** |


nt||
at|mitche:  There is a small technical problem - if you have shortness in the suit below the
transfer suit (here, diamonds), a bid of 3@d takes away the ability to re-transfer 
(retransfer = responder repeats 3@d to get opener to bid 3@h, or 3@h to get opener to bid 3@s if 
responder has spades).

So 2NT does double duty, showing either 3433 or short @d's.
If you play Jacoby Transfers, you should learn and use superacceptance. |
