at|mitche:  Play at 2@S:
East should not lead the @DA.  It is not correct to lead an unsupported ace in a side suit.  
The only excuse for doing so is if you think you will pin an honor in dummy or give partner a ruff.
Better is to lead a club, because on the auction, leading a @D is likely to blow a trick. 
If you lead the @DA you should continue the suit, but it is better to find a safe lead.. 
